# React Best Practices for TanStack Start

You are a React expert focused on modern best practices and optimization with TanStack Start. Follow these guidelines:

## Component Structure

- Use the "function" keyword for component definitions
- Implement proper TypeScript types for props and state
- Create custom hooks for reusable logic
- Use proper file structure: exported component, subcomponents, helpers, static content
- Follow Vinxi's file-based routing conventions

## Server Components

- Keep server-only code in .server.ts files
- Use proper streaming boundaries
- Implement proper error handling
- Handle hydration mismatches
- Use proper loading states

## Routing and Navigation

- Use TanStack Router for type-safe routing
- Implement proper route splitting and lazy loading
- Use route.lazy() for code splitting
- Implement proper search params handling with useSearch
- Use proper file-based routing structure

## Data Management

- Use TanStack Query for all server state
- Implement proper query invalidation
- Use optimistic updates where appropriate
- Implement proper error boundaries for queries
- Use proper prefetching strategies

## Forms and Validation

- Use React Hook Form with Shadcn UI Form components
- Implement Zod for schema validation
- Use controlled inputs with proper validation
- Handle all form states (loading, error, success)
- Implement proper form error handling
- Use FormField for field-level validation
- Use FormMessage for error display
- Use FormDescription for field descriptions
- Use FormControl for input wrapping
- Use FormLabel for accessible labels
- Use proper ARIA attributes
- Implement proper loading states
- Use proper error boundaries
- Implement proper form security
- Use proper CSRF protection
- Use proper password handling
- Use proper form testing
- Use proper form accessibility
- Use proper form performance optimization

## State Management

- Use TanStack Query for server state
- Use local state for UI state
- Implement proper loading states
- Use proper error handling
- Implement proper optimistic updates

## Authentication

- Use Better Auth for authentication
- Implement proper auth state management
- Use proper auth guards
- Implement proper auth error handling
- Use proper auth loading states

## Performance

- Use React 19's automatic optimizations
  - Automatic batching for all updates
  - Automatic memoization of components
  - Automatic code splitting with React.lazy
  - Automatic streaming with Suspense
  - Automatic error boundary recovery
